author: USA Football
description:
About USA Football: USA Football, the sport's national governing body in the United States, hosts more than 100 football training events annually offering education for coaches, skill development for players and resources for youth football league commissioners. The independent nonprofit is the official youth football development partner of the NFL, its 32 teams and the NFL Players Association. USA Football manages U.S. national teams within the sport for international competitions and provides more than $1 million annually in equipment grants and youth league volunteer background check subsidies. Endowed by the NFL and NFLPA in 2002 through the NFL Youth Football Fund, USA Football (www.usafootball.com) is chaired by former NFL team executive Carl Peterson.

Like us on Facebook Page - http://www.facebook.com/usafootball

Follow us on Twitter - https://twitter.com/usafootball

author: Flag Football Academy
description:
Get flags (https://amzn.to/2Ooickk) and cones (https://amzn.to/2q1OYOC)

Youth Flag Football Drill - One on One Flag Pulling. A one on one flag pulling drill that gives multiple repetitions in a short amount of time. This is the key to a good drill when practice time is limited. Check out http://theflagfootballplaybook.com for more.

This video details a flag pulling drill I run with my kids every practice. The drill usually only takes about 5 minutes. Depending on the number of players in each line, the kids will each get around 8-15 chances on defense. While scrimmaging will teach your kids where to be in certain situations based on the play the offensive runs, many games are lost because of poor flag pulling, despite being in the perfect position on defense. This is why repetition of the basic skills is necessary to instill good technique and confidence in your players.

Some key points are focusing on the offensive player's belt and attacking the flags with just below the hip.

This can be effective for the offense as well. Have the offense run full speed ahead instead of slowing down and trying to juke the defender. This drill should simulate the middle linebacker chasing down a ball carrier.

Adding this drill to your daily routine should payoff as your team will progressively get better throughout the season and limit the number of missed flags resulting in big plays for your opponent.

DISCLAIMER: This description contains affiliate links, which means that if you click on the link and purchase, I’ll receive a small commission. This helps support the channel and thanks for your support.

author: 40eleven
description:
This video highlights some of the boys football plays during the Fall 2011 Upward Flag Football season.  Yeah, I know it's flag, but the guys have skillz and I'm a pretty proud mom, so I'm showing them off!
  
Micah (#3) was star running back for his team so his highlights make up most the video.  
Josiah (#84) played Center, QB and Receiver.  He had fun playing with his classmate, Sam who is in a couple clips.  
Isaac (#14) played some QB and Receiver, but mostly defense.  He mastered the skill of rushing the quarterback for hurries or a loss on numerous occasions.  Defense is my favorite, so it made me proud watching him learn how to read the other team.  I also highlighted a couple of decent receptions of his on offense. 

 Yeah, I'm proud of the boys and their love for football.  Enjoy!
title: Hughes Brothers Flag Football 2011

author: iwffa
description:
Jordal Amfi Oslo Norwaylength  2:45

Valerenga Trolls 
Filmed by: Gjertrud Eia
Produced by: Johan Tillberg
Photographer - Tormod S. Vinje


The IWFFA traveled to Scandinavia in the late 90s and introduced the sport of flag football to female athletes who never caught,  threw or saw a football . Their style of play does not imitate the men, but rather demonstrates the true female style.   Diane Beruldsen / President and Founder IWFFA
Gjertrud Eia creates a documentary of Norways first Womens Flag Football team (Valerenga Trolls also known as the Oslo Trolls)  as they train outside during the 2000 winter to prepare for their first competition against Swedens Gothenburg Angels. Both teams  make it to the U.S. Key West International Championship in February 2001.

 zum Beispiel bei Nachfragen nach

Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin) Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Joo Se Hyuk (Bester ALLROUNDDEFENSIVSPIELER DES JAHRTAUSENDS),Oh Sang Eun (Korea)
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften (Dortmund 2012 ca 120 Gigabyte Videomaterial mit Spielern aus allen Teilen der Welt), Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
E-Mail an djstoni@gmx.de (alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.

Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...).

description:
Direkten Kontakt zum "Macher" der talkwithme13 - Videos auf YOUTUBE:
E-Mail: djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel auch Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove 
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin)
Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Oh Sang Eun, Korea ,
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.
Und wann darf ich SIE filmen ??????

Tennis de table Table tennis pingpong Tischtennis كرة الطاولة սեղանի թենիս mahai-tenisean настольны тэніс тенис на маса 乒乓球 乒乓球 탁구 stolni tenis bordtennis tenis de mesa lauatennis pöytätennis tenis bwrdd მაგიდის ჩოგბურთი πινγκ-πονγκ टेबल टेनिस asztalitenisz tenis meja leadóg boird borðtennis tennis da tavolo テーブルテニス ಟೇಬಲ್ ಟೆನಿಸ್ galda teniss stalo tenisas тенис на маса tafeltennis بازی پینگ پنگ tenis stołowy tênis de mesa настольный теннис стони тенис stolný tenis namizni tenis meza ya tenisi tenis sa mesa டேபிள் டென்னிஸ் stolní tenis టేబుల్ టెన్నిస్ เทเบิลเทนนิส masa tenisi настільний теніс ٹیبل ٹینس bàn đánh quần vợt טיש טעניס .

Direkten Kontakt zum "Macher" der talkwithme13 - Videos auf YOUTUBE,
E-Mail an   djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel bei Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin) Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Oh Sang Eun (Korea)
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
E-Mail an djstoni@gmx.de (alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.
Und wann darf ich SIE filmen ??????

author: Reinhard Steinbrecher
description:
Philipp Berr, der "Überraschungsmann" in Burglengenfeld hatte sich bereits den Titel im Mixed gesichert. Jetzt ging es gegen Benjamin Roesner, Neuzugang beim 2.Ligisten TV Hilpoltstein. Der war bei Bayerischen Meisterschaften U18 
schon naheezu unschlagbar und gewann sowohl 2010 als auch 2011 bei den Herren.
Doch wegen "beruflicher Belastung" lief es in dieser Saison nicht wie gewohnt...
Auf dem YOUTUBE - Kanal talkwithme13 (ein Wort ohne Pause) gibt es regelmaeßig
die Heimspiele des TV Hilpoltstein mit vielen TOPSTARS zu sehen.
Dazu Archivaufnahmen (z.b. von Ex-HIP-Star Michael Ziegler ,Felix Bindhammer und
Alexander Moest ab 1994 (!!!), sowie die diversen Endspiele bei Bayerische Schueler - und
Jugendmeisterschaften von Manuel Hoffmann oder den Auftritt von Flemming, Bindhammer, Ziegler bei den sueddeutschen Jugendmeisterschaften 2001 (!!!) im mittelfraenkischen
Adelsdorf oder den Sieg von Alexander Flemming über Jugendeuropameister Patrick Franziska beim Bundesranglistenfinale.Auf talkwithme13 ebenfalls zu finden: Die Spiele
bei den Nationalen Deutschen Meisterschaften 2010 in Trier (Benjamin Roesner gegen
Timo Boll und -im Doppel-gegen D.Ovtcharov) und Bamberg 2011.
Zusaetzlich gibt es die besten Videos von Alexander Flemming  auf Youtube-Kanal
TTCenterDD (z.B. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sr9S7vM9Yl0).
Auf den Seiten von Chris Heidingsfelder (https://www.facebook.com/search/results.php?q=Chris+Heidingsfelder&init=public) und http://www.youtube.com/user/ChrisHeidingsfelder/videos
(Die Tischtennis-Community) finden sich noch mehr Videos und aktuelle Informationen auch bezueglich z.B. Turnieren mit Felix Bindhammer, TV Hip auswaerts in Stuttgart
und deren tolle Memos mehr !!!!

author: Reinhard Steinbrecher
description:
Direkten Kontakt zum "Macher" der talkwithme13 - Videos auf YOUTUBE:
E-Mail: djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel auch Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove 
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin)
Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Oh Sang Eun, Korea ,
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.
Und wann darf ich SIE filmen ??????

author: Reinhard Steinbrecher
description:
Die jüngste Spielerin in der DEUTSCHEN DAMENNATIONALMANNSCHAFT  Sabine Winter bestritt in Dortmund bereits ihre 3.Weltmeisterschaft.
Die ehemalige Jugendeuropameisterin im Doppel gilt neben der DEUTSCHEN VIZEMEISTERIN von 2010 (Trier) Peti SOLJA als größte Nachwuchshoffnung im DTTB.
An der Seite von Kathrin Muehlbach gewann sie ebenfalls 2010 den DEUTSCHEN MEISTERTITEL IM DAMENDOPPEL.
Das Spiel von SABINE WINTER gilt als "sehr männlich und athletisch".
Sie umläuft gerne die Rückhand, um ihren grandiosen Vorhandtopspin 
"durchzupeitschen".
Dabei gibt sie nie auf, ist eine tolle Kämpferin, was ihre Matches immer
außergewöhnlich sehenswert macht.
In der Saison 2012-2013 wechselt "Bayerns bislang BESTE SPIELERIN DES
JAHRTAUSENDS" vom TSV SCHWABHAUSEN (Trainer Alexander Yahmed)
zur DJK Kolbermoor,dem frischgebackenen Aufsteiger aus der 2.Bundesliga.
Trainer ist dort der ehemalige ungarische Nationalspieler Zsolt Hollo.
Der hat mit den beiden "MANTZ-SISTERS" (Sarah und Chantal) zwei
vielversprechende JUNGSTARS unter seinen Fittichen, die durchaus in einigen
Jahren zusammen mit Sabine auch den Stamm der DTTB-Auswahl bilden könnten.
(sozusagen die "Borussia Düsseldorf" des Damentischtennis).
Es lohnt sich also, den weiteren "Karriereverlauf" von SABINE WINTER aufmerksam
zu  verfolgen, zumal sich Kolbermoor dank Zsolt Hollo längst vom Geheimtipp
zur absoluten BAYERISCHEN TISCHTENNISHOCHBURG gemausert hat.

In Dortmund mußte Sabine Winter gegen eine sehr starke Japanerin und die
Polin Natalia Partyka antreten, zwei Gegnerinnen, die in der Weltrangliste deutlich
vor ihr plaziert sind.Siege wurden daher diesmal nicht von ihr erwartet.
Dennoch war sie bereits beim ersten WM-Spiel in Dortmund von sovielen begeisterten 
Zuschauern umringt, dass die meisten in der Nebenhalle keinen Platz mehr bekamen
(auch der fleißige Sabine Winter - "Videograph" kam nur mit Mühe zu einigen bewegten
Bildern). 
Im Spiel um Platz 8 bekam sie dann aber ihre ganz große Bühne,
die geschichtstraechtige Dortmunder Westfalenhalle, wo 1989 Jörg Rosskopf und
Steffen "SPEEDY" Fetzner den ersten und bislang einzigen WM-Titel im Herrendoppel
für den DTTB erkämpft hatten.
Ihre Gegnerin aus Polen, die wohl BESTE HANDYCAP -TISCHTENNISSPOTLERIN
DER WELT (Armamputation) hatte sich während der gesamten WM als brilliante
Technikerin mit hoher Spielintelligenz und absolutem Siegeswillen praesentiert.
Die besten Vorraussetzungen also für das Match, das kurz vor dem Finale
der Herren CHINA gegen DEUTSCHLAND fuer die richtige Stimmung unter
tausenden begeisterter Fans sorgen sollte.
Unabhängig vom Spielausgang ein weiterer glanzvoller Höhepunkt im
Tischtennisleben von Kolbermoor-Neuzugang Sabine Winter ...

E-Mail: djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel auch Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove 
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin)
Waldner, Joergen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu,Joo Se Hyuk (Bester ALLROUNDDEFENSIVSPIELER DES JAHRTAUSENDS)  Oh Sang Eun, Korea ,
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften (Dortmund 2012 mit ca 120 Gigabyte Videomaterial
und Spielern aus aller Welt), Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.

description:
Explore the world of table tennis, watch this young and very talented fighter from Kasachstan and many uprising talents, You may have not seen in the focus before...The name of the young player of Kasachstan is
KIRILL GERASSIMENKO .On the other side of the table: CHANG HOI MA from
Macauchina.
If You see persons on the video that You know, please make notes in the comments.
Thank You for Your help !!!!

Direkten Kontakt zum "Macher" der talkwithme13 - Videos auf YOUTUBE,
E-Mail an   djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel bei Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin) Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Joo Se Hyuk (Bester ALLROUNDDEFENSIVSPIELER DES JAHRTAUSENDS),Oh Sang Eun (Korea)
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften (Dortmund 2012 ca 120 Gigabyte Videomaterial mit Spielern aus allen Teilen der Welt), Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
E-Mail an djstoni@gmx.de (alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.

author: Giovanni Di Pietro
description:
http://www.giwafitness.it/it/catalogue/productDetail.aspx?area=relax&idmaster=2926&title=Tavolo%20Ping%20Pong%20TRAINING%20OUTDOOR%20+%20set%20racchette%20e%20palline%20omaggioGarlando Guarda il video e acquista il tuo tavolo da ping pong. 

Garlando Tavolo Ping Pong TRAINING OUTDOOR + set racchette e palline omaggio 

Modello per esterno, provvisto di misure regolamentari da torneo, interamente costruito con materiali e componenti resistenti agli agenti atmosferici ed estremamente robusti, che assicurano al tavolo una durata eccezionale anche se sottoposto alle intemperie.
Le caratteristiche di questo modello garlando lo rendono adatto per l'uso privato e il gioco di livello amatoriale

Disponibile con piano di gioco blu e telaio nero.
Pieghevole, è facile da spostare e permette di essere riposto risparmiando spazio. 

Campo di gioco in resina stratificata spessore mm. 4. Si tratta di un materiale estremamente duro, in grado di resistere agli urti della racchetta senza rovinarsi. Linee bianche serigrafate all'interno del materiale del piano gioco: permangono inalterate anche dopo molto tempo di permanenza all'aperto. Finitura antiriflesso per giocare a lungo senza affaticare la vista. 

La robusta struttura metallica dello spessore di cm. 3,6 che circonda interamente il piano di gioco, oltre a migliorare l'estetica del tavolo, è fissato ad alta pressione ed è in un pezzo unico anziché nei quattro pezzi (uno per ogni lato) previsti dagli standard abituali. Ciò, oltre a migliorare aumenta nel contempo la rigidità e la compattezza del piano.
Telaio in metallo con struttura tubolare mm. 25 con verniciatura a polvere impermeabile.
Le gambe sono dotate di 4 ruote diametro cm. 12,5. Due delle ruote sono in grado di ruotare a 360 gradi per permettere la completa mobilità del ping pong e il massimo comfort in fase di spostamento, anche su terreni accidentati, mentre le due restanti, fisse, agiscono da freno quando il tavolo è fermo.

Rete e tendirete permanenti sia quando il tavolo è in posizione di gioco sia quando è piegato. E' quindi eliminata l'antipatica necessità di smontarli e rimontarli ogni volta. 
Barra metallica posizionata sotto il campo di gioco in corrispondenza dell'unione dei due piani con doppia funzione:
a) Possibilità di allenarsi da soli: quando uno dei due piani è sollevato la barra metallica annulla completamente il dislivello impedendo che la pallina possa cadere. 
b) Funzione di sicurezza: rendendo la distanza tra i due piani inferiore a 11 centimetri, come previsto dalla legge, la barra impedisce che un bambino si introduca in mezzo ai due piani.

Porta-racchette incorporati su entrambi i lati per un maggior comfort in fase di gioco (ognuno può contenere 2 racchette e 4 palline).
L'assenza della traversa di collegamento delle gambe consente l'utilizzo del tavolo da parte di persone con mobilità ridotta (sulla sedia a rotelle).
Training Outdoor è conforme alle norme europee armonizzate sulla sicurezza dei tavoli da ping pong EN 14468-1/2.
Garanzia di due anni contro i difetti di fabbricazione.

description:
Hab hier ein Paar Bälle abgewehrt, bitte nicht vergessen ich bin Angriffsspieler :P

Wichtig hierbei ist:
-Ball sehr tief nehmen ,denndort hat er weniger Spin und ist langsamer
-eine hackende Bewegung ausführen 
-eher eine gerade Bewegung als eine Bogenbewegung machen ( ähnlich wie beim Topspin bloß andere Richtung )
-Ball eher neben dem Köper treffen
-Ball möglichst flach und lang halten

 zum Beispiel auch Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove 
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin)
Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Oh Sang Eun, Korea ,
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-

author: Reinhard Steinbrecher
description:
Direkten Kontakt zum "Macher" der talkwithme13 - Videos auf YOUTUBE:
E-Mail: djstoni@gmx.de
 zum Beispiel auch Nachfragen nach
exclusiven eigenen Aufnahmen von Ma Long, Wang Hao, Zhang Jike , Chen Qi ,Jan-Ove 
Ding Ning (Weltmeisterin)
Waldner, Jorgen Persson, Mikael Appelgren, Robert Svensson
Olympiasieger Ryu, Oh Sang Eun, Korea ,
Matsudaira, Fukuhara (Japan)
und allen "europäischen TT-Weltmeistern" seit 1989 -Gatien,Werner Schlager, Rosskopf-Fetzner-
sowie natuerlich Timo Boll, Ovtcharov, Suess, Jugendweltmeister Patrick Baum und
den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.
Und wann darf ich SIE filmen ??????

den vierfachen DEUTSCHEN MEISTER der Jahre 2011 u.2012 Bastian Steger inclusive seiner
Erfolge seit 1994 (Bayer.Jugendmeisterschaften !!!!!!)
dazu Weltmeisterschaften, Europameisterschaft 2009, Deutsche Meisterschaften,
German Open 2006 Bayreuth, 2010 Berlin, Championsleague, DTTL,
TT-Show-Kämpfen (Exhibition) Waldner, Persson,Orlowski-Panski
Saive-Zhengcai (great) A.Grubba, J.P. Gatien , Promorav-Korbel u.v.a.
Deutsche DJK Meisterschaften, Deutsche Eichkreuzmeisterschaften und das vermutlich
weltweit umfassendste Videoarchiv über Tischtennis in Bayern (über 20 Bayerische Meisterschaften !!!)
Veterans-Seniorensport: WM 2006 Bremen, EM 1995 (die allererste!!!) in Wien, 1997 in Prag
2011 Liberec, DM Neustadt-Aisch u.v.a.
alle Videos zum Selbstkostenpreis-kein kommerzielles Interesse-
aber großes Interesse an Tausch-Videos,  auch TT-Sammelobjekte (Telefonkarten-Briefmarken-TT-Songs auf Vinyl und CD- TT-Bücher-Zeitschriften, möglichst alt oder ausländisch...
Autogramme etc.
Sie sind auch "tischtennisverrückt" ???
Auf der Facebookseite Table Tennis finden sie 260 (Stand 16.03.2012) großartige Tischtennissportler von Waldner, Boll bis zu allen deutschen Nachwuchsstars
(Franziska, Solja, Ort, Schreiner, Jost, Matthias, ...). 
Kontakt über  https://www.facebook.com/ReinhardSteinbrecher.
Und wann darf ich SIE filmen ??????

Polands TT-LEGEND, who played German First League for many years
(TTC Grenzau)German Open Winner 1984 ( this great sportsman we all miss, he died tooooo early 2005 - cancer
19:14 The Empire backed by 4 colleages and on a fith guy on the right side
behind a Videocam: Richard Guegel from Heroldsbach, Germany.
It is told, that he never paid for entrance. He only put the Videocamerastuff
on his shoulder. Obviously in 1984 no privat  person in moscow owned a videocam. So everybody was sure, this man was from TV and all doors were opened for the funny sportsman...
Amuesant am Rand: In Moskau als Schlachtenbummler vor Ort: Anton Stadler
Neumarkt-TV Jahn  Nuernberg-Legende) und Schmalfilmer !!!!!) Paul Link Sen.

liesen, dass dieser man ein Stativ mit einer modernen Videocam über der
Schulter trug, dass er ohne Eintrittskarte überall Zugang hatte und, wie im

このボウリング動画チャンネルは『旧来のボウリング概念』をぶっ壊し【新世界なボウリング】を知って頂く活動を、健全な事業として行っている二人の挑戦物語です。

巷に広がる、ボーリングなのかボウリングなのか？まだボウリングの魅力に気づいていない方々から、ボウリングのコツや投げ方、カーブやフック、ローダウン投法などの情報を真剣にネット上で探している方まで、

このボウリングチャンネルを通じて様々なニーズに応えようと、ボウリング動画の公開や、リアルなセンターでのボウリングレッスンなどを行っています！！

そして更には、ボウリング動画を見て楽しんでいる方だけでなく、オンライン上でのボウリングレッスンとして、【無料メール動画レッスン】も現在配信しています。(^-^)

author: mrbowling300
description:
Please be sure to stop by http://forums.mrbowling300.com to discuss this and other great bowling topics!

$280,000 SOCIETY BANK PBA NATIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP
Ducat's Imperial Lanes, Toledo, Ohio, Mar 11-17, 1990
Jim Pencak's Second Victory A "Major"; Wins Society Bank PBA Nat'l Championship

On this St. Patrick's Day, it was, fittingly, a battle for the green in the $280,000 Society Bank PBA National Championship at Ducat's Imperial Lanes. When the smoke finally cleared, it was Jim Pencak who enjoyed the "luck 'o the Irish" in donning the green champion's blazer and pocketing the $54,000 greenbacks for his second PBA title and first "major."

Pencak, Mayfield Heights, Ohio, won four games and topped Chris Warren in the title match, 223-214, to gain a three-year exemption to the Firestone Tournament of Champions.

"I've worked a long time to get to this point and now things are falling into place," Pencak said. "This is quite a start to my career," the 10-year PBA member joked.

Both finalists spared to open the title game, then Pencak posted a three-bagger, spare and strike to lead by 10 in the sixth frame. Warren then knotted the match in the eighth with his own three-bagger. After sparing in the ninth, he left the difficult 6-7-10 split on his first 10th-frame shot, but converted it. Pencak then got up in his 10th needing only eight, spare and strike to clinch. He struck on his first ball and the rest was simply a formality.

"I was relieved I didn't have to shoot a (10th frame) spare," Pencak said. "The best mark is always a strike. This title means a lot since it's a major, but my first win will always be special, too," Pencak recounted. "I made a big move in changing balls in my second game and felt if I could get out of the gate, everything would be all right." Pencak was 8-0 in his last two championship round appearances in PBA singles competition, with his first win coming from the fourth-seeded position at the LaMode Classic in Green Bay, Wis., last summer.

The opening game of the ABC Sports-televised finals was a tough, 183182, victory Pencak eked out against reigning PBA Player of the Year Amleto Monacelli of Venezuela. Monacelli had won the previous week's tournament at Columbus, Ohio, and needed a double in his 10th frame to advance here, but left a solid 8-pin on his first shot of the 10th frame.

Next up for Pencak was first-time finalist Doug Kent of Canandaigua, N.Y., who bowed, 267-172. In the semifinal game, Pencak opened with a four-bagger against 1986 PBA National Champion Tom Crites of Tampa, Fla., and cruised home, 227-191. Crites earned $15,000 for third, Kent collected $10,000 and Monacelli $8,000.

CHAMPIONSHIP ROUND

Pos.  Name, City/State Total Amount

1  Jim Pencak, Mayfield Heights, Ohio 900 (4 games) $54,000
2  Chris Warren, Dallas 214 (1 game) 28,000
3  Tom Crites, Tampa, Fla. 192 (1 game) 15,000
4  Doug Kent, Canandaigua, N.Y. 172 (1 game) 10,000
5  Amleto Monacelli, Venezuela 182 (1 game) 8,000

PLAYOFF RESULTS-Pencak defeated Monacelli, 183-182; Pencak defeated Kent, 267-172; Pencak defeated Crites, 227-192; and in the championship game, Pencak defeated Warren, 223-214.
title: 1990 PBA National Championship

author: mrbowling300
description:
Please be sure to stop by http://forums.mrbowling300.com to discuss this and other great bowling topics!

$135,000 PBA NATIONAL CHAMPIONSHIP
Imperial Lanes, Toledo, Ohio, Mar 1-7, 1981
Holy Toledo! Anthony Again

Having already won the PBA National Championship a record three times (1973, 1974 and 1975), Earl Anthony added another to his collection by outlasting Ernie Schlegel, 242-237, in a tense, spirited championship match in the $135,000 PBA National Championship in Toledo, Ohio.

Anthony could not claim victory until Schlegel, shooting last and needing a strike to win, left a 2-pin on a shot light to the headpin.

Anthony had kept the door open for Schlegel by leaving the 1-3-6-10 spare combination in the 10th frame which he converted. Still, as he sat down to watch his destiny being decided by his opponent, Anthony prepared for what could have been another in a long series of second place finishes.

"It isn't often you can sit on the bench and win," said Anthony after the nerve-racking triumph.

"I really wanted to win this bad because it gives me four National Championships and it's going to be hard for anyone to top that," he added, savoring the prestige of a major tournament win as well as the $21,000 first prize.

It was also Anthony's third win in his last four tournaments on the Winter Tour and he had finished third in the event he didn't win.

Anthony took control of the 56-game qualifying and match play event after the fourth round and went on to build a 285-pin cushion over Dick Weber, the 51-year-old bowling legend and hero of a generation past. Weber had out-maneuvered Schlegel for the second-seeded position with Schlegel getting third, followed by two-time PBA National Champion Dave Davis, in fourth, and Gary Dickinson, runner-up in the 1980 National, in fifth.

It was a veteran and much revered finals cast with three having already been elected to the PBA Hall of Fame (Anthony, Weber and Davis) and the other two debating about who was the youngest (both 37, Schlegel was 15 days younger than Dickinson).

Despite a foul midway through the opening match, Davis edged Dickinson, 204-203. Then Schlegel stepped in to crush Davis, 245-171, and eliminate Weber, 236-204, to move into position to win the first major title of his career.

As nearly 2,000 people watched first-hand at Imperial Lanes in the enthusiastic bowling city of Toledo, Anthony and Schlegel stood even after five frames. Anthony pulled ahead with strikes in the seventh, eighth and ninth frames which proved to be enough to win the 22nd annual National Championship of the Professional Bowlers Association.

TELEVISED FINALS

Pos.  Name, City/State Total Amount

1  Earl Anthony, Dublin, Calif. 242 (1 game) $21,000
2  Ernie Schlegel, Vancouver, U.S.A. 718 (3 games) 11,000
3  Dick Weber, St. Louis 204 (1 game) 6,000
4  Dave Davis, Tinton Falls, N.J. 375 (2 games) 5,000
5  Gary Dickinson, Burleson, Texas 203 (1 game) 4,500

PLAYOFF RESULTS - Davis defeated Dickinson, 204-203; Schlegel defeated Davis, 245-171; Schlegel defeated Weber, 236-204; and in the championship match, Anthony defeated Schlegel, 242-237.
title: 1981 PBA National Championship

author: ボウリング 投げ方のコツを動画で！新世界ボウリング.com
description:
★無料の動画ボウリングレッスン講座→http://glocalshare-37.info/cs2r/lp2/　
★総合サイト→ http://glocalshare-37.info/cs2r/blogg/

このボウリング動画チャンネルは『旧来のボウリング概念』をぶっ壊し【新世界なボウリング】を知って頂く活動を、健全な事業として行っている二人の挑戦物語です。

巷に広がる、ボーリングなのかボウリングなのか？まだボウリングの魅力に気づいていない方々から、ボウリングのコツや投げ方、カーブやフック、ローダウン投法などの情報を真剣にネット上で探している方まで、

このボウリングチャンネルを通じて様々なニーズに応えようと、ボウリング動画の公開や、リアルなセンターでのボウリングレッスンなどを行っています！！

そして更には、ボウリング動画を見て楽しんでいる方だけでなく、オンライン上でのボウリングレッスンとして、【無料メール動画レッスン】も現在配信しています。(^-^)

まずは、下記の公式サイトでこの新世界ボウリング.com の実態を知らべて見て欲しいと思います！！

それでは、また別の動画でお会いしましょう♪


【公式HPサイト】 http://shinsekaibowling.glocalshare-37.info/　

【佐藤の毎日ブログ】 http://glocalshare-37.info/cs2r/blogg/

【Facebookページ】 https://www.facebook.com/shinsekaibowling

author: mrbowling300
description:
Please be sure to stop by http://forums.mrbowling300.com to discuss this and other great bowling topics!

$250,000 BPAA U.S. OPEN
Bowl One, Troy, MI, Apr 2-8, 1995
Husted Wins 2nd BPAA U.S. Open With "Show At The Joe"

Leading qualifier Dave Husted captured his second Bowling Proprietors' Association of America (BPAA) U.S. Open crown via a 266-245 survival test against first-time finalist Paul Koehler. Contested before a PBA record paid attendance of 7,212 at Detroit's Joe Louis Arena, Husted has now collected four PBA wins since announcing his "semi-retired" status last spring. His $46,000 first prize will no doubt comfort the Milwaukie, Ore., pro's waning participation on the Tour.

Both championship finalists started with turkeys, and Husted broke first with a spare in the fourth. Koehler (pronounced Kay-lor), Stuart, Fla., continued striking through six frames, spared, and then doubled. Husted wrenched his back mid-game, but painstakingly struck on his next six shots. Koehler's failure to convert the 5-7 leave in his 10th frame left him with the $24,000 second prize, but a new legion of admirers.

Regarding this bookend "major" accompanying his 1982 BPAA U.S. Open, Husted said, "That title was special because it was my first win and my parents were there. I'm at the point now in my career where I don't know how many times I'll have the opportunity to win. It's time for me to move on with my life and my recent successes haven't changed my desire to spend more time with my family."

The Motor City madness began with fourth-seeded Steve Hoskins downing Dave D'Entremont, 231-212. Hoskins then defeated Parker Bohn III, Jackson, N.J., 256-216, before being turned back by Koehler in a thriller, 278-256. Hoskins, Tarpon Springs, Fla., could have advanced in a roll-off by striking out in his 10th frame, but his first shot didn't connect, and left him with the $14,000 third prize. Bohn earned $10,500 for fourth place.

Husted had compiled an impressive 273-pin margin over second seed Koehler after the 56-game tournament format. The 240-man BPAA U.S. Open field is made up of 144 leading PBA Tour players and 96 BPAA center qualifiers, and who were led by 20th-place finisher Cliff Connors of Tempe, Ariz., who earned a $500 bonus and trophy for pacing the BPAA contingent (which also included four international bowlers) after 32 games.

CHAMPIONSHIP ROUND

Pos.  Name, City/State Total Amount

1  Dave Husted, Milwaukie, OR 266 (1 game) $46,000
2  Paul Koehler, Stuart, FL 523 (2 games) 24,000
3  Steve Hoskins, Tarpon Springs, FL 743 (3 games) 14,000
4  Parker Bohn III, Jackson, NJ 216 (1 game) 10,500
5  Dave D'Entremont, Middleburg Heights, OH 212 (1 game) 8,500

PLAYOFF RESULTS-Hoskins defeated D'Entremont, 231-212; Hoskins defeated Bohn, 256-216; Koehler defeated Hoskins, 278-256; and in the championship game, Husted defeated Koehler, 266-245.
title: 1995 BPAA U.S. Open

description:
http://howtobowling.blogspot.com has much more from Bob! Do not miss out on this important message from Bob of Bob's Bowling Tips fame! Bob IS the Big Lebowski, The Dude...or whatever you want to call him. If you like my tips, please subscribe to my blog at:  http://HowToBowling.blogspot.com . Also, please subscribe to my video channel at: http://YouTube.com/BobsBowlingTips .

Your Friend,
Bob






... Bowling Tips. 
How to bowling.
How to Bowl

Polishing Your Balls
Bob's Bowling Tips

Polishing your Balls. I say balls because let's face it we all have more than just one. I have two but my buddy Mark gave me twenty bucks so I let him play with one. There are many ways to polish your balls. They have machines that will do it for you, they make them warm and shiny but I like going old school and just using a dry towel.They also make a bag you can put your balls in that will shine them as you walk. This seems a little wasteful to me but to each his own. I personally like to use rubbing alchohol to polish my ball. I say polish when actually it's more cleaning than polishing. You don't want to let oil build up on your balls. It will effect the performance and hamper your ability to achieve your goal. There are many great products for cleaning your balls just visit my recommend site's. So remember keep your balls clean and you too can be a WINNER! Happy Bowling

author: Georgiesbowlerama
description: Sorry youtube viewers, it's been a while since I've uploaded a video last weekend. The delay was because I didn't go bowling last weekend and chose to do something else. I don't know why my bowling ball gets stuck in the pinsetter. When I come here to bowl at Wildfire Lanes in Las Vegas, NV I have to get a secondary bowling ball for backup because my bowling ball gets stuck here every time I bowl here. Wildfire Lanes needs an upgrade to their pinsetters! I actually bowled here when I was sick, and I wanted to because I was feeling much better. I was suffering from a mysterious illness or possibly an infection, I don't know. The symptoms I had were: Fever and a Sore Throat. After a weekend of not bowling, and getting sick, I'm back!
title: I'm Back! Bowling at Wildfire Lanes Part 1/4: Getting the hang of bowling again!

description: Match 2 of the PBA's 2000 Parker Bohn Classic.  6th place qualifier Jason Hurd has alreadydefeated 6 seed Steve Wilson and 7 seed Jeff Lizzi to advance to this match agains 4 seed Brian Voss and 5 seed Rick Steelsmith.  The winner of this match will advance to face 2 seed Ryan Shafer and 3 seed Pete Weber, with the winner of that match facing Brian Himmler for the title.  Noteworthy to me is what a bastardization these lanes are.  Brunswick 2000 ball returns, Brunswick early '70s era Starshield masking units, and AMF 82/30 pinsetters.  What a clusterf**k of a bowling center.  Originally telecast Saturday, February 12, 2000 on ESPN.  Phil Ferguson on play-by-play.  Marshall Holman on color.

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
The fourth and final spot for the PBA World Championship finals will be determined this Sunday when the PBA World Championship Mike Aulby Division Final, airs at 1 p.m. ET Sunday on ESPN from the South Point Bowling Center in Las Vegas. The field of 16 finalists will be down to the final four for the Sunday, Jan. 15 battle for the $50,000 first prize, the Earl Anthony Trophy and the PBA Tour's first major title of the 2011-12 season.

Australia's two-handed star, Jason Belmonte, leads the field of four players in Sunday's Mike Aulby Division finals. He will be joined in the Aulby elimination round by Brian Kretzer of Dayton, Ohio; rookie Josh Blanchard of Gilbert, Ariz., and Mike Fagan of Dallas.

Belmonte hasn't won a title since his first PBA Tour victory in the 2009 Bowling Foundation Long Island Classic propelled him to 2009-09 PBA Rookie of the Year honors. Kretzer won his only PBA Tour title in the 2010 Go RVing Match Play Championship. Fagan is a two-time title winner. His most recent victory was in the 2010 One A Day Dick Weber Open. Blanchard, a former Wichita State University star, joined the PBA in October and won a PBA West Region Non-Champions tournament in Reno, Nev., in his first appearance as a member. Sunday's telecast will be his PBA Tour television debut.

The Aulby Division winner will join Finland's Osku Palermaa, Ryan Shafer of Horseheads, N.Y., and Sean Rash of Montgomery, Ill., in the World Championship finals on Sunday, Jan. 15, at 1 p.m. ET on ESPN.

In Sunday's division finals, all four players will bowl a one-game match. The player with the lowest score will be eliminated. The three survivors will bowl another game, with the low man knocked out. The two finalists will bowl a final game, with the survivor advancing to the World Championship finals.

The Mike Aulby finals is named after the PBA Hall of Famer, 29-time PBA Tour champion and winner of the 1979 and 1985 PBA National Championships.

Three easy steps to enhance your PBA World Championship telecast experience:

1. Free Xtra Frame Mike Aulby finals preview show (now available on pba.com's Xtra Frame) - Tune into pba.com's Xtra Frame for interviews with the finalists as they give their insight into strategy and equipment selection. All World Championship preview shows on Xtra Frame are available the Wednesday before each Sunday ESPN telecast for free.

2. Sunday, 1 p.m. ET -- ESPN telecast of the Mike Aulby Division final from South Point in Las Vegas.

3. Sunday 2:30 p.m. ET -- Xtra Frame post-tournament show interviews the winning player and provides in-depth ball rep analysis of the winner's equipment selection and ball preparation. (Xtra subscription information is available on the pba.com Xtra Frame page.)

Bowling fans can provide their feedback on World Championship telecasts through PBA's social networking platforms on Facebook and Twitter.
title: 2011 - 2012 PBA World Championship (Mike Aulby Division) - Match 03

2011年10月28日（金）
Round 1武蔵村山店にてパーフェクトゲームを達成しました。
この日は父の久方ぶりにボウリングしています。
父の前でパーフェクトを達成できて非常ににうれしく思います。
ボウリング人生１５年目。ようやく出ました。
遅すぎたパーフェクト達成になりました。

投球は意外にも不安定で、やっとの思いで倒れたシーンもあり、
永久シードの中山律子プロも恐れる１０フレームは意外に精神的に冷静に投げれましたが、私にとっての「魔のフレーム」は６フレ。ちょうど折り返しの時が一番怖かったかな。
このパーフェクトを期に更なる目標に向けしっかり日々練習に励みたいと思います。
昨日の品川プリンスホテルボウリングセンターの成績が嘘のように今日は安定していました。
これからもがんばりますので、ボウリング場で見かけたら声かけてください。

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
The PBA Hardwick Division, which will air at 1 p.m. ET on ESPN, is the second of four eliminator rounds that will eventually trim the PBA World Championship field of 16 finalists down to four for the Sunday, Jan. 15, battle for the $50,000 first prize, the Earl Anthony Trophy and the PBA Tour's first major title of the 2011-12 season.

Tom Smallwood of Saginaw, Mich., who won his only PBA Tour title in the 2009 PBA World Championship, heads the field of four players who will do battle this week. Joining him in the Hardwick final from the South Point Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas will be Venezuela's Ildemaro Ruiz, Colombia's Andres Gomez and 25-year PBA Tour veteran Ryan Shafer of Horseheads, N.Y.

Smallwood became an instant hero among America's blue-collar work force when he defeated former PBA Player of the Year Wes Malott for the 2009 PBA World Championship. Smallwood, who had lost his job with General Motors, had decided to pursue his dream to become a professional bowler and stunned the bowling world with his upset victory in Wichita, Kan. Last season, he won $100,000 as runner-up to Mika Kovuniemi in the PBA Tournament of Champions.

Both South American players are trying for their first PBA Tour titles. Ruiz, is making his PBA television debut and Shafer is trying for his fifth Tour title.

In Sunday's divisional finals, all four players will bowl a one-game match. The player with the lowest score will be eliminated. The three survivors will bowl another game, with the low man knocked out. The two finalists will bowl a final game, with the survivor advancing to the World Championship finals.

The Billy Hardwick finals are named after the PBA Hall of Famer and two-time PBA Player of the Year who won 18 Tour titles including the 1963 PBA National Championship and 1965 PBA Tournament of Champions.


Three easy steps to enhance your PBA World Championship telecast experience:


1. Free Xtra Frame Billy Hardwick finals preview show (now available on pba.com's Xtra Frame) - Tune into pba.com's Xtra Frame for interviews with the finalists as they give their insight into strategy and equipment selection. All World Championship preview shows on Xtra Frame are available the Wednesday before each Sunday ESPN telecast for free.


2. Sunday, 1 p.m. ET -- ESPN telecast of Billy Hardwick Division final from South Point in Las Vegas.


3. Sunday 2:30 p.m. ET -- Xtra Frame post-tournament show interviews the winning player and provides in-depth ball rep analysis of the winner's equipment selection and ball preparation. (Xtra subscription information is available on the pba.com Xtra Frame page.)
title: 2011 - 2012 PBA World Championship (Billy Hardwick Division) - Match 02

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
Barnes Leads Field of Four into Sunday's Alka-Seltzer Plus USBC Masters Finals on ESPN
by Bill Vint January 27, 2012 15:53
HENDERSON, Nev. - Chris Barnes of Double Oak, Texas, earned the top seed for Sunday's live televised finals at the 2012 Alka Seltzer Plus Liquid Gels United States Bowling Congress Masters on Friday.

Barnes went 6-0 in the double-elimination match-play bracket at Sunset Station's Strike Zone Bowling Center and is now one more victory away from claiming his first career Masters title. The finals will be broadcast live on ESPN at 12:30 p.m. Eastern on Sunday.

Barnes earned the top seed by virtue of an 806-743 victory over Mike Fagan of Dallas. Fagan, who was previously unbeaten, is the No. 2 seed for the finals. Rounding out the telecast is No. 3 seed Dan MacLelland of Canada and No. 4 seed Bryon Smith of Roseburg, Ore.

"Things definitely fell my way today," said Barnes, who finished as the runner-up to Walter Ray Williams Jr. at 2004 and 2010 Masters. "This is where I wanted to be at the start of the week. After having Walter Ray fire a 268 and a 290 at me when I was the top seed previously, I feel like this time it's my turn. I'm a big believer that everything evens out, and I'm a long way from being even."

A victory by Barnes would make him the third Professional Bowlers Association Grand Slam winner in history, joining bowling greats Mike Aulby and Norm Duke. The Grand Slam is made up of the four majors on the PBA Tour - the USBC Masters, PBA Tournament of Champions, U.S. Open and the PBA National/World Championship.

"Winning this event is definitely a bucket list item for me," Barnes said. "This tournament is the most important one on my career list right now."

Fagan plowed through five consecutive opponents before running into Barnes in the final match to determine the top seed for the TV show. He said he was just happy that match happened when it did.

"I feel good, and I'm just happy that match with Chris came at the end and not earlier in the bracket," said Fagan, who will be seeking his first major title. "I'm just trying to play my game and not worry about any of my competitors. That's the frame of mind I need to keep for the TV show."

As for MacLelland, he knew getting to the championship would be a grind after winning his first match and then dropping into the losers bracket. He had to win seven matches in the losers bracket, including a 746-690 victory over Chris Warren of Grants Pass, Ore., that locked up a spot on the telecast.

"My body isn't quite what it used to be, and I knew it was going to be a grind coming into today," said MacLelland, who was a three-time collegiate bowler of the year at Saginaw Valley State. "I kept telling myself that I could do it, and I basically willed myself to the show."

Smith made the finals by overcoming a 29-pin deficit heading into the final game, rallying for a 660-625 victory against Chris Loschetter of Avon, Ohio. It's the first time Smith has made a TV appearance since 2004 and his lone professional title came at the 2003 USBC Masters.

"My heart rate went up a couple times today, and when I was down in that last game my heart rate went up again," Smith said. "Come Sunday, I'm sure there will be some nerves. When this isn't something you do on a regular basis anymore, it can be a bit more nerve wrecking."

The week began with 305 of the best players in the world vying for a piece of the $250,000 prize fund and $50,000 first-place prize.
title: 2012 PBA Alka Seltzer Plus Liquid Gels USBC Masters - Match 03

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
The PBA Hardwick Division, which will air at 1 p.m. ET on ESPN, is the second of four eliminator rounds that will eventually trim the PBA World Championship field of 16 finalists down to four for the Sunday, Jan. 15, battle for the $50,000 first prize, the Earl Anthony Trophy and the PBA Tour's first major title of the 2011-12 season.

Tom Smallwood of Saginaw, Mich., who won his only PBA Tour title in the 2009 PBA World Championship, heads the field of four players who will do battle this week. Joining him in the Hardwick final from the South Point Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas will be Venezuela's Ildemaro Ruiz, Colombia's Andres Gomez and 25-year PBA Tour veteran Ryan Shafer of Horseheads, N.Y.

Smallwood became an instant hero among America's blue-collar work force when he defeated former PBA Player of the Year Wes Malott for the 2009 PBA World Championship. Smallwood, who had lost his job with General Motors, had decided to pursue his dream to become a professional bowler and stunned the bowling world with his upset victory in Wichita, Kan. Last season, he won $100,000 as runner-up to Mika Kovuniemi in the PBA Tournament of Champions.

Both South American players are trying for their first PBA Tour titles. Ruiz, is making his PBA television debut and Shafer is trying for his fifth Tour title.

In Sunday's divisional finals, all four players will bowl a one-game match. The player with the lowest score will be eliminated. The three survivors will bowl another game, with the low man knocked out. The two finalists will bowl a final game, with the survivor advancing to the World Championship finals.

The Billy Hardwick finals are named after the PBA Hall of Famer and two-time PBA Player of the Year who won 18 Tour titles including the 1963 PBA National Championship and 1965 PBA Tournament of Champions.


Three easy steps to enhance your PBA World Championship telecast experience:


1. Free Xtra Frame Billy Hardwick finals preview show (now available on pba.com's Xtra Frame) - Tune into pba.com's Xtra Frame for interviews with the finalists as they give their insight into strategy and equipment selection. All World Championship preview shows on Xtra Frame are available the Wednesday before each Sunday ESPN telecast for free.


2. Sunday, 1 p.m. ET -- ESPN telecast of Billy Hardwick Division final from South Point in Las Vegas.


3. Sunday 2:30 p.m. ET -- Xtra Frame post-tournament show interviews the winning player and provides in-depth ball rep analysis of the winner's equipment selection and ball preparation. (Xtra subscription information is available on the pba.com Xtra Frame page.)
title: 2011 - 2012 PBA World Championship (Billy Hardwick Division) - Match 01

In this episode of Bowler to Bowler, where one bowler interviews another, IAB's own Jason Belmonte interviews the legendary Norm Duke.  Unlike most of our other Bowler to Bowler interviews, this is a more casual sit down interview and we take a close look into the bowling career of Norm Duke.  This is part 1 of 2.

Brought to you by The International Art of Bowling.


www.iabowling.com

www.iabowling.tv
title: Norm Duke and Jason Belmonte - Bowler to Bowler Interview Part 1

author: Jim Osdale
description:
Steltronic scoring will be used for the 3rd consecutive year at the USBC Women's Championship Tournament in Reno Nevada at the National Bowling Stadium. 

Over 30,000 bowlers expected to compete in this year's tournament lasting more than 3 months with up to 78 lanes running a single event. The tournament history started back in 1916 in St. Louis Missouri, while taking a break from 1943-45 because of World War II.

Steltronic thanks the USBC for continuing this great tournament for everyone to enjoy.

Steltronic Scoring: (909) 971-9656
info@steltronicscoring.com

author: BowlingOldies
description: Championship Match of the PBA's 2000 Parker Bohn Classic.  Previously in Match 3, 3rd place qualifier Pete Weber defeated 6 seed Jason Hurd (who won the first two matches) and 2 seed Ryan Shafer.  So here is Weber in the title match against tournament leader Brian Himmler.  Noteworthy to me is what a bastardization these lanes are.  Brunswick 2000 ball returns, Brunswick early '70s era Starshield masking units, and AMF 82/30 pinsetters.  What a clusterf**k of a bowling center.  Originally telecast Saturday, February 12, 2000 on ESPN.  Phil Ferguson on play-by-play.  Marshall Holman on color.
keywords: ['bowling', 'pro bowling', 'pete weber', 'brian himmler', 'phil ferguson', 'marshall holman', 'classic tv', 'sports', 'pba']
title: 2000 Parker Bohn Classic - Championship Match

author: irishpogi
description: Here is  part 1 of the final match of the 2011 Staten Island USBC Masters event and it was contested at Rab's Country Lanes in Staten Island, NY.  The pattern used was the 2011 USBC Open Championships pattern which is 41 feet in length and sport bowling compliant.  The contestants here are Vinny D'Ambrosio III [winner of the contenders bracket] and Lou Gaudio Jr.  Vinny is using the Storm Marvel Solid, the Storm Virtual Gravity Nano, and the Storm Ice plastic ball. Lou used a Storm Victory Road Solid pin over the ring finger cg kicked right with balance hole.
title: 2011 Staten Island USBC Masters Tournament: Final Match: D'Ambrosio vs Gaudio part 1

author: ☆Wii ωiz™☆
description:
Ever wondered what kind of Paradise you will experience on a Tropical Island? It's a paridise unlike any other with Wii Sports Resort. The only game that introduces the Wii Motion Plus accessory for increased precision and accuracy. Join me ☆Wii ωiz™☆, as I take on every challenge and game that awaits us on this Island.

Stamps - Bowling: Standard Game
1: Gobble Gobble (Score a Turkey (3 Strikes in a Row))
2: Split Spare (Simple, Pick up a Split (Try to leave an Easy one you can make for ex. "3-10"))
3: High Roller (Finish a Game with a Score of 200 or Higher) 
4: Pin Dropper (Go through One Game with Only Strikes and Spares (No Misses))
5: Perfect Game (Get All 12 Strikes in One Game for the Perfect Mark of 300)

Stamps - Bowling: 100-pin Game
1: Super Strike (Get a Strike, Simple Right? (If you have lots of power and curve on it))
2: Split Spare 
3: Off the Wall (Make the ball bounce off the Guard for a Strike (Trust Me, It's NOT that Easy))
4: Secret Strike (If you're Lucky, Get the Ball Rolling on the Guard Throughout the Roll, then you'll hear a detonator sound and All the Pins will Fall)
5: Pin Dropper

Stamps - Bowling: Spin Control
1: One For All (Roll the Ball and make sure it safely passes through the Obsticles and hit a pin in one Roll in Every Frame)
2: Split-Spare 
3: Head First (Knock down the Head Pin (1-Pin) in Every Frame)
4: English Major (Score 170 or higher without touching the Barriers)
5: Pin Dropper
title: ☆Wii ωiz™☆ Plays - Wii Sports Resort [8] (Bowling)

author: Ashley Nicole Dunn
description:
This video is best viewed in full HD.

Thanks to the USBC and the Coaches and Staff of Team USA for hosting a world class tournament.

This is the last game of the 5th six game qualifying block for the men. The pattern for the block was the WTBA London which is 44' long and a fairly heavy volume.

Going into this last qualifying block 15 y/o Wesley Low Jr. of Palmdale, CA & 14 y/o Kamron Doyle of Brentwood, TN were both either in position to complete the tournament as one of the top two Juniors, automatically earning a position on Junior Team USA, or at a minimum maintain a position among the top five Juniors, giving themselves a chance at becoming an at large choice of the selection committee.

Up until this game both youngsters had been on track, with Wesley having a slightly better day. There were a couple other older Juniors that had been doing well and steadily moving up. This last game it seemed would make or break earning a position on the team outright, which is always a safer bet than having your fate in the hands of the Selection Committee.

Two of the contenders were bowling on the pair with them, AJ Chapman & Dominic Partipil. Mickey Preston is there also, and had nearly lead the entire tournament for the first three qualifying blocks, but had ran into carry issues that had dropped him nearly out of contention.

Watch as these two young phenoms battle for every pin.

Also in view on the adjacent pair to the left is Matthew Farber with the front 11 strikes going for a perfect game. Bowling with him is Scott Norton, recent two time PBA National Titlist and Nathan Bohr, also a PBA National Titlist.

We appreciate you for stopping by our channel, but most importantly thanks for watching. Make sure to hit that SUBSCRIBE button if you haven't already so you can be updated as we  upload new exciting youth bowling videos.

Follow US Youth Bowling on Twitter https://twitter.com/USYouthBowling

Check out US Youth Bowling on the web. Our site & blog should be finishing up in the next couple of weeks. There is some content available now that helps describe who we are and our purpose, visit now http://usyouthbowling.com

Like US Youth Bowling on Facebook https://www.facebook.com/USYouthBowling

We hope you enjoyed the video.

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
Barnes Leads Field of Four into Sunday's Alka-Seltzer Plus USBC Masters Finals on ESPN
by Bill Vint January 27, 2012 15:53
HENDERSON, Nev. - Chris Barnes of Double Oak, Texas, earned the top seed for Sunday's live televised finals at the 2012 Alka Seltzer Plus Liquid Gels United States Bowling Congress Masters on Friday.

Barnes went 6-0 in the double-elimination match-play bracket at Sunset Station's Strike Zone Bowling Center and is now one more victory away from claiming his first career Masters title. The finals will be broadcast live on ESPN at 12:30 p.m. Eastern on Sunday.

Barnes earned the top seed by virtue of an 806-743 victory over Mike Fagan of Dallas. Fagan, who was previously unbeaten, is the No. 2 seed for the finals. Rounding out the telecast is No. 3 seed Dan MacLelland of Canada and No. 4 seed Bryon Smith of Roseburg, Ore.

"Things definitely fell my way today," said Barnes, who finished as the runner-up to Walter Ray Williams Jr. at 2004 and 2010 Masters. "This is where I wanted to be at the start of the week. After having Walter Ray fire a 268 and a 290 at me when I was the top seed previously, I feel like this time it's my turn. I'm a big believer that everything evens out, and I'm a long way from being even."

A victory by Barnes would make him the third Professional Bowlers Association Grand Slam winner in history, joining bowling greats Mike Aulby and Norm Duke. The Grand Slam is made up of the four majors on the PBA Tour - the USBC Masters, PBA Tournament of Champions, U.S. Open and the PBA National/World Championship.

"Winning this event is definitely a bucket list item for me," Barnes said. "This tournament is the most important one on my career list right now."

Fagan plowed through five consecutive opponents before running into Barnes in the final match to determine the top seed for the TV show. He said he was just happy that match happened when it did.

"I feel good, and I'm just happy that match with Chris came at the end and not earlier in the bracket," said Fagan, who will be seeking his first major title. "I'm just trying to play my game and not worry about any of my competitors. That's the frame of mind I need to keep for the TV show."

As for MacLelland, he knew getting to the championship would be a grind after winning his first match and then dropping into the losers bracket. He had to win seven matches in the losers bracket, including a 746-690 victory over Chris Warren of Grants Pass, Ore., that locked up a spot on the telecast.

"My body isn't quite what it used to be, and I knew it was going to be a grind coming into today," said MacLelland, who was a three-time collegiate bowler of the year at Saginaw Valley State. "I kept telling myself that I could do it, and I basically willed myself to the show."

Smith made the finals by overcoming a 29-pin deficit heading into the final game, rallying for a 660-625 victory against Chris Loschetter of Avon, Ohio. It's the first time Smith has made a TV appearance since 2004 and his lone professional title came at the 2003 USBC Masters.

"My heart rate went up a couple times today, and when I was down in that last game my heart rate went up again," Smith said. "Come Sunday, I'm sure there will be some nerves. When this isn't something you do on a regular basis anymore, it can be a bit more nerve wrecking."

The week began with 305 of the best players in the world vying for a piece of the $250,000 prize fund and $50,000 first-place prize.
title: 2012 PBA Alka Seltzer Plus Liquid Gels USBC Masters - Match 02

author: bowlerdude
description:
Norm Duke..................................................................................................................................................





 soundly defeats Michael Fagan 278-168.
Sunday, February 8, 2009
Fountain Bowl, Fountain Valley, CA

When it comes down to victory and defeat, every man is alone in his task to face down ten white pins.  Even with tens of peoples watching in the crowd and hundreds of thousands more on television sets across the nation, he is alone when it comes down to making the shot.  I saw this intense focus in every players' eyes that hinted at a certain lonely detachment from the whole surrounding and total focus on the task at hand.

My sister and I got to congratulate Norm right after the show while he was smoking a cigarette in the secluded area outside. Upon seeing my sister and me, he warmly walked towards us down the ramp to meet us.  I just wanted to shake his hand and he shook both of our hands and thanked us for our sign.

What a great guy.  Congratulations Norm!  May many more titles fall upon you.




Pardon the shakiness, I tried my best to keep it steady.  I also ran out of batteries, so the video cuts off where it does.
title: Norm Duke speaks at 2009 Dick Weber Open

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
The fourth and final spot for the PBA World Championship finals will be determined this Sunday when the PBA World Championship Mike Aulby Division Final, airs at 1 p.m. ET Sunday on ESPN from the South Point Bowling Center in Las Vegas. The field of 16 finalists will be down to the final four for the Sunday, Jan. 15 battle for the $50,000 first prize, the Earl Anthony Trophy and the PBA Tour's first major title of the 2011-12 season.

Australia's two-handed star, Jason Belmonte, leads the field of four players in Sunday's Mike Aulby Division finals. He will be joined in the Aulby elimination round by Brian Kretzer of Dayton, Ohio; rookie Josh Blanchard of Gilbert, Ariz., and Mike Fagan of Dallas.

Belmonte hasn't won a title since his first PBA Tour victory in the 2009 Bowling Foundation Long Island Classic propelled him to 2009-09 PBA Rookie of the Year honors. Kretzer won his only PBA Tour title in the 2010 Go RVing Match Play Championship. Fagan is a two-time title winner. His most recent victory was in the 2010 One A Day Dick Weber Open. Blanchard, a former Wichita State University star, joined the PBA in October and won a PBA West Region Non-Champions tournament in Reno, Nev., in his first appearance as a member. Sunday's telecast will be his PBA Tour television debut.

The Aulby Division winner will join Finland's Osku Palermaa, Ryan Shafer of Horseheads, N.Y., and Sean Rash of Montgomery, Ill., in the World Championship finals on Sunday, Jan. 15, at 1 p.m. ET on ESPN.

In Sunday's division finals, all four players will bowl a one-game match. The player with the lowest score will be eliminated. The three survivors will bowl another game, with the low man knocked out. The two finalists will bowl a final game, with the survivor advancing to the World Championship finals.

The Mike Aulby finals is named after the PBA Hall of Famer, 29-time PBA Tour champion and winner of the 1979 and 1985 PBA National Championships.

Three easy steps to enhance your PBA World Championship telecast experience:

1. Free Xtra Frame Mike Aulby finals preview show (now available on pba.com's Xtra Frame) - Tune into pba.com's Xtra Frame for interviews with the finalists as they give their insight into strategy and equipment selection. All World Championship preview shows on Xtra Frame are available the Wednesday before each Sunday ESPN telecast for free.

2. Sunday, 1 p.m. ET -- ESPN telecast of the Mike Aulby Division final from South Point in Las Vegas.

3. Sunday 2:30 p.m. ET -- Xtra Frame post-tournament show interviews the winning player and provides in-depth ball rep analysis of the winner's equipment selection and ball preparation. (Xtra subscription information is available on the pba.com Xtra Frame page.)

Bowling fans can provide their feedback on World Championship telecasts through PBA's social networking platforms on Facebook and Twitter.
title: 2011 - 2012 PBA World Championship (Mike Aulby Division) - Match 02

author: SundaysR4Bowling
description:
SUNDAY, DEC. 26, 1 P.M. EASTERN

The PBA GEICO Shark Championship is the fifth telecast of the 2010-11 Lumber Liquidators PBA Tour season and will air this Sunday, Dec. 26 at 1 p.m. Eastern on ESPN from South Point Bowling Center in Las Vegas.

For the second consecutive week the telecast will feature an international-laden stepladder finals field where four countries are represented: Australia, Finland, Canada and U.S. It is also the first PBA stepladder final to feature two players who use a two-handed delivery (Jason Belmonte and Osku Palermaa).

The GEICO Shark Championship is the last of the five "animal" pattern events conducted as part of the PBA World Series of Bowling. The final event from the World Series of Bowling will be the "USA vs. The World" team event on Jan. 9 at 1 p.m. Eastern on ESPN.

Eugene McCune won the season-opening Brunswick Pro Bowling Cheetah Championship, followed by Bill O'Neill winning the Pepsi Viper Championship, Scott Norton then won the Chameleon Championship and Yung-Jin Gu became the first Korean to win a PBA Tour title in the Scorpion Championship.

PBA GEICO Shark Championship stepladder finals qualifiers:

Match 1:

No. 5 Mike Fagan, Patchogue, N.Y. vs. No. 4 Jason Belmonte, Australia

Match 2:

Winner Match 1 vs. No. 3 Tom Smallwood, Saginaw, Mich.

Match 3:

Winner Match 2 vs. No. 2 Osku Palermaa, Finland

Championship Match

Winner of Match 3 vs. No. 1 Dan MacLelland, Canada

- Fagan will be trying for his third PBA Tour title. His last win was in the One A Day Dick Weber Open last season.

- Australian two-hander and 2008-09 PBA Rookie of the Year Belmonte will be trying for his second title. He won his first in The Bowling Foundation Long Island Classic in March 2009. Belmonte finished third in last week's Scorpion Championship.

- 2009 PBA World Championship winner Smallwood will try for his second Tour title.

- Considered to be Europe's best two-handed player, Palermaa will be trying for his first Tour title. His previous best finish was third in the 2010 Etonic Don Johnson Eliminator last March and fifth in the recent Chameleon Championship.

- PBA Tour rookie MacLelland tries for his first Tour title. He finished fifth in last week's Scorpion Championship.

Tournament Recap: Two 6-game qualifying rounds with top 16 advancing to 9-game match play round.

First round leader (after 6 games qualifying): Mike DeVaney, Murietta, Calif., 1,487

Second round leader (after 12 games qualifying): Belmonte, 2,851

Third round leader (after 21 games qualifying and match play): MacLelland, 4,901
title: 2010 - 2011 PBA GEICO Shark Championship (Week 05) - Part 02

description: In the first match of the 1998 ABC Masters, Parker Bohn III threw 12 strikes in a row for a perfect 300 game.  Making this 300 stand out from the others on TV was that he was bowling against two competitors, meaning that instead of bowling two frames and sitting down, he bowled just one.  Facing Parker in this match were fellow lefties Mike Mullin and Chris Sand...not surprising, given the locale: The Reno National Bowling Stadium (for Lefties).  Part 2 of 2.
title: 1998 ABC Masters - Parker Bohn III shoots 300 (Part 2)
